To extend the manual log review I wrote a Pthon script to automatically scan Linux log files for suspicious activity (failed logins,
unknown users, etc.)
The Python script opens the Linux_2k.log file and reads its lines into a list called logs.
It then takes lines 200 to 500 and puts them in a new list, subset_logs. The script checkseach line in this subset for keywords like 
"Failed password" "authentication failure" and "user unknown" or "invalid user."
